revision.text:
{{nihongo|'''Ube Shrine'''|宇倍神社|Ube-jinja}} is a [[Shinto]] shrine located at [[Tottori, Tottori|Tottori]] in [[Tottori Prefecture]], [[Japan]]. It was the ''ichinomiya of [[Inaba province]].<ref>Ponsonby-Fane, Richard. (1964). ''Visiting Famous Shrines in Japan,'' pp. 329-351.</ref> 

From 1871 through 1946, the Ube Shrine was officially designated one of the {{nihongo|''Kokuhei Chūsha''|国幣中社|}}, meaning that it stood in the second rank of government supported shrines.  These shrines were construed to have national significance; and the ''Kokuhei Chūsha'' encompassed 47 sanctuaries, including Ube-jinja

== See also== 
* [[List of Shinto shrines]]
* [[Modern system of ranked Shinto Shrines]]
* [[Inaba Maru]]

==Notes==
{{reflist|1}}

==References==
